-- Magna May Build Infinity With Daimler Parts, Auto News Reports
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2011-12-18T16:16:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-18/magna-may-build-infinity-with-daimler-parts-auto-news-reports.html
Magna Steyr Fahrzeugtechnik may
build an entry-level car for  Nissan Motor Co. (7201) ’s Infiniti premium
brand using  Daimler AG  parts, Automotive News Europe  reported ,
citing unidentified company officials.  Magna could build 60,000 cars a year at its plant in Graz,
 Austria , using pre-assembled parts including engines from
Daimler’s Mercedes-Benz brand, the report said. Magna and Nissan
are expected to finalize such a contract in early 2012, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
